article.headline: Rice 52, Princeton 41
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Morris Almond scored 21 points Thursday night to lead Rice to a 52-41 victory over Princeton. The Owls (6-7) used a pair of 7-0 runs in the second half to defeat Princeton (2-10). After Rice took a 31-19 lead early in the second half, the Tigers came back with an 11-4 run to cut the lead to 32-30. Almond then hit a 3-pointer, but Noah Savage answered with a 3-pointer of his own. The Owls then went on another 7-0 run. Almond scored 11 of his 21 points in the first half as the Owls took a 24-19 lead. Lorenzo Williams added 12 points and J.R. Harrison added 11 for the Owls. Luke Owings led Princeton with 11 points and Edwin Buffmire added 10. Rice shot 51 percent from the field to 31 percent for Princeton.
